                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "STTA",
                "ACTIV",
                "BCINT"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The   stacked-foil   method.   The",
                " reaction yields were  measured  by  determining  the",
                " radioactivity   of   the  ten-minute  copper-62  and",
                " three-hour copper-61 nuclei which results  from  the",
                " (gamma,n) and (gamma,2n) processes, respectively, in",
                " copper-63.  The number of photoneutrons ejected from",
                " the  copper  foil  was  determined  by  counting the",
                " residual  radioactivity  of  the  Cu-62  and   Cu-61",
                " isotopes with 4pi scintillation counter."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The natural-copper foils used in the  (gamma,n)  runs",
                " were 1.25-inch diameter disks 40 mg/cm2 thick, while",
                " the enriched foils were 0.5 inch x 0.75-inch  strips",
                " totaling 65 mg/cm2. Highly-enriched copper-63 foils:",
                " copper  oxide  containing  99.4%  copper-63.   Foils",
                " ranging  in  thickness  from  3  to  16  mg/cm2  and",
                " totaling 130 mg/cm2 were made."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " 4Pi  scintillation  counter:  the   foil   was",
                " sandwiched  between  two  flat  anthracene crystals,",
                " 1.-inch square and 0.125-inch thick,  backed by  two",
                " DuMont 6292 photomultipliers."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "UNFLD",
                "PHDIF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The  number  of  photoneutrons  ejected",
                " from  the copper foil was determined by counting the",
                " residual  radioactivity  of  the  Cu-62  and   Cu-61",
                " isotopes with 4pi scintillation counter.  Activation",
                " points were taken at  2  MeV  intervals.  The  cross",
                " sections   were  computed  from  experimental  yield",
                " curves  by  applying  the  photon-difference  method",
                " using  bremsstrahlung  distributions calculated at 2",
                " MeV intervals for  a  0.025-radiation-length  copper",
                " radiator."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The cross   sections   given   were   corrected   for",
                " contributions  caused  by  the  competing three-hour",
                " activity of Cu-61 (from  Cu-63(g,2n)  reaction)  for",
                " twelve-hour    Cu-64   activity   (from   Cu-65(g,n)",
                " reaction) which was evaluated by counting  it  after",
                " decay  of  the  three-hour  Cu-61  activity and then",
                " correcting by extrapolating  back  to  the  original",
                " Cu-64  activity  and  for multiple scattering of the",
                " primary electrons from Linac in the foils  increases",
                " the  effective  path  length  of  the bremsstrahlung",
                " quanta and electrons in the rear  foil  relative  to",
                " the  first  (a correction for this was applied which",
                " varied from 4.0 to 0.4% from 12 to 36 MeV)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Experimental values were found for the absolute cross",
                " section  of  both  Cu-63(gamma,n)   and   (gamma,2n)",
                " reactions  versus gamma-quanta energy from threshold",
                " to 36 MeV.  Statistical and systematic  errors  were",
                " limited by the use of:",
                "  (a) the direct electron beam of the Stanford 36 MeV",
                "      linear     accelerator,     which      produced",
                "      bremsstrahlung  immediately  before  and within",
                "      the copper foils under bombardment,",
                "  (b) an electron-beam collector which  recorded  the",
                "      total accumulated charge in the incident flux,",
                "  (c) a  4pi scintillation counter which measured the",
                "      activity of the resultant Cu-62 and Cu-61,",
                "  (d) electroplated   foils   of   separated    Cu-63",
                "      isotopes."
              ]
            }
          ],
